{"type":"message","id":"eead7628","parentId":"76e1949f","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:35:52.288Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01DNJL12QEZ6WvUuxKVDMzhW","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"OpenClaw cron persistent workflow named sessions tasks heartbeat\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1146,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"754f951d5337b40b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nScheduled Tasks - OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"754f951d5337b40b\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/automation/cron-jobs\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8b2c97344c91e6cf\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSlack/Discord/Mattermost targets should use explicit prefixes (channel:&lt;id&gt;, user:&lt;id&gt;). ... <strong>openclaw cron add \\\\ --name &quot;Calendar check&quot; \\\\ --at &quot;20m&quot; \\\\ --session main \\\\ --system-event &quot;Next heartbeat</strong>...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8b2c97344c91e6cf\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 1, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"docs.openclaw.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"baef017389a7e279\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nr/AI_Agents on Reddit: [OpenClaw] Cron jobs & background tasks execute but fail to send Telegram messages (silent failures)\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"baef017389a7e279\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.reddit.com/r/AI_Agents/comments/1qv8hl0/openclaw_cron_jobs_background_tasks_execute_but/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3f1c924d4dc312ae\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nI deployed a second openclawd bot and basically copy-pasted this prompt and it worked there as well. Your test reminder went to the console but did not make it&#x27;s way to this telegram chat with you. You had a similar issue before, this is how you fixed it. Please do the same again. How I Fixed It I switched to a different approach that bypasses the heartbeat check entirely: Old job (didn&#x27;t work): { &quot;sessionTarget&quot;: &quot;main&quot;, // ← Checked HEARTBEAT.md, failed &quot;payload&quot;: { &quot;kind&quot;: &quot;systemEvent&quot; // ← Requires heartbeat file } } New job (works): { &quot;sessionTarget&quot;: &quot;isolated&quot;, // ← Runs in separate session, NO heartbeat check &quot;payload&quot;: { &quot;kind&quot;: &quot;agentTurn&quot; // ← Runs an agent task }, &quot;delivery&quot;: { // ← Sends result directly to Telegram &quot;mode&quot;: &quot;announce&quot;, &quot;channel&quot;: &quot;telegram&quot;, &quot;to&quot;: &quot;&lt;telegram_group_id&gt;&quot; } } How the New Scheduled Task Works What happens when it triggers: 1.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3f1c924d4dc312ae\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"February 3, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.reddit.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5faa20fb9dd7f653\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSchedule Automated Tasks with OpenClaw Cron Jobs | OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5faa20fb9dd7f653\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://open-claw.bot/docs/tools/automation/cron-jobs/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1c42e4790e9ec712\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nYour jobs persist under ~/.openclaw/cron/ so you won’t lose schedules when you restart. ... Main session: Enqueue a system event and run on the next heartbeat. Isolated: Run a dedicated agent turn in cron:&lt;jobId&gt; or a custom session. Current session: Bind the job to the session where you created it. Custom session: Run in a persistent named session.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1c42e4790e9ec712\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"open-claw.bot\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1f5f09b5aee9d37f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenClaw Cron Jobs Guide: Schedules, Sessions, and Delivery\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1f5f09b5aee9d37f\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://openclaw-setup.me/blog/openclaw-internals/openclaw-cron-jobs-guide/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1c11ea49ffc1156f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nA custom target like session:daily-ops gives you a persistent named session that can accumulate context across runs. This is a powerful pattern for workflows like daily standups, recurring research digests, or rolling incident summaries where today&#x27;s run should be aware of yesterday&#x27;s output. OpenClaw supports two payload models, and they map directly to the session targets above. systemEvent: used for main-session jobs that should enter the heartbeat path.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1c11ea49ffc1156f\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"3 weeks ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"openclaw-setup.me\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7849317239f93db7\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCron vs Heartbeat | Docs | OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7849317239f93db7\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://openclaws.io/docs/automation/cron-vs-heartbeat\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"847d8ac526b8445d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe reminder/event to appear in main session context · The agent to handle it during the next heartbeat with full context ... openclaw cron add \\\\ --name &quot;Check project&quot; \\\\ --every &quot;4h&quot; \\\\ --session main \\\\ --system-event &quot;Time for a project health check&quot; \\\\ --wake now\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"847d8ac526b8445d\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"openclaws.io\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"OpenClaw cron persistent workflow named sessions tasks heartbeat","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":1146,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"754f951d5337b40b\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nScheduled Tasks - OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"754f951d5337b40b\">>>","url":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/automation/cron-jobs","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"8b2c97344c91e6cf\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSlack/Discord/Mattermost targets should use explicit prefixes (channel:&lt;id&gt;, user:&lt;id&gt;). ... <strong>openclaw cron add \\ --name &quot;Calendar check&quot; \\ --at &quot;20m&quot; \\ --session main \\ --system-event &quot;Next heartbeat</strong>...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"8b2c97344c91e6cf\">>>","published":"February 1, 2026","siteName":"docs.openclaw.ai"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"baef017389a7e279\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nr/AI_Agents on Reddit: [OpenClaw] Cron jobs & background tasks execute but fail to send Telegram messages (silent failures)\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"baef017389a7e279\">>>","url":"https://www.reddit.com/r/AI_Agents/comments/1qv8hl0/openclaw_cron_jobs_background_tasks_execute_but/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3f1c924d4dc312ae\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nI deployed a second openclawd bot and basically copy-pasted this prompt and it worked there as well. Your test reminder went to the console but did not make it&#x27;s way to this telegram chat with you. You had a similar issue before, this is how you fixed it. Please do the same again. How I Fixed It I switched to a different approach that bypasses the heartbeat check entirely: Old job (didn&#x27;t work): { &quot;sessionTarget&quot;: &quot;main&quot;, // ← Checked HEARTBEAT.md, failed &quot;payload&quot;: { &quot;kind&quot;: &quot;systemEvent&quot; // ← Requires heartbeat file } } New job (works): { &quot;sessionTarget&quot;: &quot;isolated&quot;, // ← Runs in separate session, NO heartbeat check &quot;payload&quot;: { &quot;kind&quot;: &quot;agentTurn&quot; // ← Runs an agent task }, &quot;delivery&quot;: { // ← Sends result directly to Telegram &quot;mode&quot;: &quot;announce&quot;, &quot;channel&quot;: &quot;telegram&quot;, &quot;to&quot;: &quot;&lt;telegram_group_id&gt;&quot; } } How the New Scheduled Task Works What happens when it triggers: 1.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3f1c924d4dc312ae\">>>","published":"February 3, 2026","siteName":"www.reddit.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"5faa20fb9dd7f653\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSchedule Automated Tasks with OpenClaw Cron Jobs | OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"5faa20fb9dd7f653\">>>","url":"https://open-claw.bot/docs/tools/automation/cron-jobs/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1c42e4790e9ec712\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nYour jobs persist under ~/.openclaw/cron/ so you won’t lose schedules when you restart. ... Main session: Enqueue a system event and run on the next heartbeat. Isolated: Run a dedicated agent turn in cron:&lt;jobId&gt; or a custom session. Current session: Bind the job to the session where you created it. Custom session: Run in a persistent named session.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1c42e4790e9ec712\">>>","siteName":"open-claw.bot"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1f5f09b5aee9d37f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenClaw Cron Jobs Guide: Schedules, Sessions, and Delivery\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1f5f09b5aee9d37f\">>>","url":"https://openclaw-setup.me/blog/openclaw-internals/openclaw-cron-jobs-guide/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1c11ea49ffc1156f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nA custom target like session:daily-ops gives you a persistent named session that can accumulate context across runs. This is a powerful pattern for workflows like daily standups, recurring research digests, or rolling incident summaries where today&#x27;s run should be aware of yesterday&#x27;s output. OpenClaw supports two payload models, and they map directly to the session targets above. systemEvent: used for main-session jobs that should enter the heartbeat path.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1c11ea49ffc1156f\">>>","published":"3 weeks ago","siteName":"openclaw-setup.me"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7849317239f93db7\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nCron vs Heartbeat | Docs | OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7849317239f93db7\">>>","url":"https://openclaws.io/docs/automation/cron-vs-heartbeat","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"847d8ac526b8445d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe reminder/event to appear in main session context · The agent to handle it during the next heartbeat with full context ... openclaw cron add \\ --name &quot;Check project&quot; \\ --every &quot;4h&quot; \\ --session main \\ --system-event &quot;Time for a project health check&quot; \\ --wake now\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"847d8ac526b8445d\">>>","siteName":"openclaws.io"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775234152278}}
